obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4174)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4174&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Emigration`
  line `Act, 1983.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India and applies also to citizens of India outside India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint and`
  line `different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference in any such`
  line `provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the commencement of that`
  line provision.
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 30th December, 1983, vide notification No. S.O. 940(E), dated 30th December, 1983, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4175)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4175&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "certificate" means a certificate of registration issued under section 11;`
  line
  line `(b) "conveyance" includes a vessel, vehicle, country-craft and an aircraft;`
  line
  line `(c) "dependent" means any person who is related to an emigrant and is dependent on that`
  line emigrant;
  line
  line `(d) "emigrant" means any citizen of India who intends to emigrate, or emigrates, or has emigrated`
  line `but does not include--`
  line
  line `(i) a dependent of an emigrant, whether such dependent accompanies that emigrant, or`
  line `departs subsequently for the purpose of joining that emigrant in the country to which that`
  line `emigrant has lawfully emigrated;`
  line
  line `(ii) any person who has resided outside India at any time after attaining the age of eighteen`
  line `years, for not less than three years or the spouse or child of such person;`
  line
  line `(e) "emigrant conveyance" means any conveyance specially chartered for conveyance of`
  line `emigrants or for conveying emigrants exceeding such number as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, declare that any conveyance`
  line `conveying emigrants to such place as may be specified in the notification shall not be deemed to be`
  line `an emigrant conveyance;`
  line
  line `(f) "emigrate" and "emigration" mean the departure out of India of any person with a view to`
  line `taking up any employment (whether or not under an agreement or other arrangements to take up such`
  line `employment and whether with or without the assistance of a recruiting agent or employer) in any`
  line `country or place outside India;`
  line
  line `(g) "employer" means any person providing or offering to provide, employment in any country or`
  line `place outside India;`
  line
  line `(h) "employment" means any service, occupation or engagement (not being service, occupation`
  line `or engagement under the Central Government or a State Government), in any kind of work within the`
  line `meaning of clause (o), for wages or for reward, and all its grammatical variations and cognate`
  line `expressions shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(i) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(j) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "Protector of Emigrants" means a Protector of Emigrants appointed under section 3 and`
  line `includes a person authorised under section 5;`
  line
  line `(l) "recruiting agent" means a person engaged in India in the business of recruitment for an`
  line `employer and representing such employer with respect to any matter in relation to such recruitment`
  line `including dealings with persons so recruited or desiring to be so recruited;`
  line
  line `(m) "recruitment" includes the issuing of any advertisement for the purpose of recruitment, the`
  line `offering by advertisement to secure or assist in securing any employment in any country or place`
  line `outside India and the entering into any correspondence, negotiation, agreement or arrangement with`
  line `any individual for or in relation to the employment of such individual in any country or place outside`
  line India;
  line
  line `(n) "registering authority" means the officer appointed under section 9 to be the registering`
  line `authority for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "work" means--`
  line
  line `(i) any unskilled work, including any form of industrial or agricultural labour;`
  line
  line `(ii) any domestic service;`
  line
  line `(iii) any service, not being a service in a managerial capacity, in any hotel, restaurant, teahouse`
  line `or other place of public resort;`
  line
  line `(iv) work as a driver of a truck or other vehicle, mechanic, technician or skilled labourer or`
  line artisan;
  line
  line `(v) work as an office assistant or accountant or typist or stenographer or salesman, or nurse or`
  line `operator of any machine;`
  line
  line `(vi) work in connection with, or for the purposes of, any cinema, exhibition or entertainment;`
  line
  line `(vii) any such work of a professional or of any other nature as the Central Government may,`
  line `having regard to the need for the protection of citizens of India who may be employed in such`
  line `work outside India and other relevant circumstances, specify by notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, if satisfied that it is necessary so to do having regard`
  line `to the conditions of service applicable with respect to employment in any of the aforementioned`
  line `categories of work or any sub-category thereof, whether generally or in relation to any particular`
  line `country or place and other relevant circumstances, declare by notification that such category of work`
  line `or sub-category of work shall not be deemed to be work within the meaning of this definition.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any law which is not in force in any area shall, in relation to that area,`
  line `be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4176)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Protectors of Emigrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4176&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, appoint a Protector`
  line `General of Emigrants and as many Protectors of Emigrants, as it deems fit, for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by general or special order, define the area to which the authority`
  line `of a Protector of Emigrants so appointed shall extend and, where two or more Protectors of Emigrants are`
  line `appointed for the same area, also provide, by such order, for the distribution and allocation of the work to`
  line `be performed under this Act in relation to such area.`
  line
  line `(3) The Protectors of Emigrants shall perform the functions assigned to them by or under this Act`
  line `under the general superintendence and control of the Protector General of Emigrants.`
  line
  line `(4) The Protector General of Emigrants may, in addition to the special function assigned to him by or`
  line `under this Act, perform all or any of the functions assigned to any Protector of Emigrants.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4177)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `General duties of Protectors of Emigrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4177&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions of this Act, every`
  line `Protector of Emigrants shall, in addition to the special duties assigned to him by or under this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) protect and aid with his advice all intending emigrants and emigrants;`
  line
  line `(b) cause, so far as he can, all the provisions of this Act and of the rules made thereunder to be`
  line `complied with;`
  line
  line `(c) inspect, to such extent and in such manner as may be prescribed--`
  line
  line `(i) any emigrant conveyance, or`
  line
  line `(ii) any other conveyance if he has reason to believe that any intending emigrants or`
  line `emigrants are proceeding from, or returning to, India to or from a place outside India by such`
  line `other conveyance;`
  line
  line `(d) inquire into the treatment received by emigrants during their voyage or journey to, and during`
  line `the period of their residence in the country to which they emigrated and also during the return voyage`
  line `or journey to India and report thereon to the Protector General of Emigrants or such other authority as`
  line `may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(e) aid and advise, so far as he reasonably can, emigrants who have returned to India.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4178)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to authorise persons to exercise functions of a Protector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4178&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government`
  line `may, if satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the interest of emigrants or intending emigrants, authorise`
  line `any person to perform all or any of the functions of a Protector of Emigrants under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4179)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Emigration check-posts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4179&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government considers that, with a view to`
  line `preventing or checking the contravention of the provisions of this Act, it is necessary so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification, set up such number of emigration check-posts at such places as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by general or special order made in this behalf, appoint an officer`
  line `of the Central Government or of a State Government to be an officer in charge of an emigration checkpost`
  line `set up under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) An officer in charge of an emigration check-post shall be subject to the general control and`
  line `supervision of the Protector of Emigrants within the local limits of whose jurisdiction that emigration`
  line `check-post is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4180)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Other emigration officers and staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4180&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may appoint such other officers`
  line `and employees (hereinafter referred to as the emigration officers and emigration employees), as it may`
  line `think fit, to assist the Protector General of Emigrants and the Protectors of Emigrants in the performance`
  line `of their duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4181)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Emigration officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4181&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Protector General of Emigrants, Protectors of`
  line `Emigrants, the officers in charge of emigration check-posts, emigration officers and emigration`
  line `employees appointed under this Act shall be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4182)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Registering authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4182&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, appoint the Protector`
  line `General of Emigrants or any other officer of that Government of a rank higher than that of a Protector of`
  line `Emigrants to be the registering authority for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (4183)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `No person to function as recruiting agent without a valid certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4183&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act, no recruiting agent shall, after the commencement of this Act, commence or carry on`
  line `the business of recruitment except under and in accordance with a certificate issued in that behalf by the`
  line `registering authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person carrying on the business of recruiting agent immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act may continue to carry on such business without such a certificate for a period`
  line `of one month from such commencement, and if he has made an application for such certificate under this`
  line `Act within the said period of one month and such application is in the prescribed form and contains the`
  line `prescribed particulars, till the disposal of such application by the registering authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (4184)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Application for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4184&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for registration shall be made to the`
  line `registering authority in such form and shall contain such particulars as to the applicants financial`
  line `soundness, trustworthiness, premises at which he intends to carry on his business, facilities at his disposal`
  line `for recruitment, his antecedents (including information as to whether any certificate had been issued to`
  line `him under this Chapter earlier and if so, whether such certificate had been cancelled) and previous`
  line `experience, if any, of recruitment and other relevant matters as may be prescribed and shall be`
  line `accompanied by a receipt evidencing the payment of the prescribed fee and an affidavit giving his current`
  line `financial standing and an undertaking in the form prescribed to the effect that in the event of any`
  line `information furnished in or along with the application for registration being found to be false or incorrect`
  line `in any respect, the certificate shall be liable to be cancelled at any time in accordance with the procedure`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall be entertained under this sub-section from a person disqualified`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 14 till the expiry of the period of such disqualification.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of such application, the registering authority shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the application is not in the prescribed form or does not contain any of the prescribed`
  line `particulars, return the application to the applicant;`
  line
  line `(b) if the application is in the prescribed form and contains the prescribed particulars, inform the`
  line `applicant that he is eligible for the grant of the certificate applied for and, after giving the applicant an`
  line `opportunity to be heard, determine, under sub-section (3), the amount of the security which the`
  line `applicant shall furnish.`
  line
  line `(3) The registering authority shall, for securing the due performance of the terms and conditions of`
  line `the certificate proposed to be issued by it under sub-section (2) to an applicant and for securing`
  line `compliance with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder and for meeting expenses which`
  line `may have to be incurred in the event of the repatriation to India of any of the emigrants who may be`
  line `recruited by the applicant determine, in accordance with the rules made in this behalf, the amount of`
  line `security (not being in any case less than one lakh of rupees) which shall be furnished by the applicant.`
  line
  line `(4) If an applicant furnishes in the prescribed manner the amount of security determined under`
  line `sub-section (3) within a period of one month from the date on which the registering authority requires him`
  line `to furnish such security, he shall be issued the certificate applied for by him together with an endorsement`
  line `thereon to the effect that the security required has been furnished by him.`
  line
  line `(5) If an applicant fails to furnish the security required to be furnished by him within the period`
  line `specified in sub-section (4), his application shall be deemed to have been rejected by the registering`
  line `authority on the date of expiry of that period.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (4185)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Terms and conditions of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4185&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `A certificate issued under section 11 shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) in such form as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) valid for such period not exceeding five years as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a certificate may be issued for a period shorter than the prescribed period--`
  line
  line `(i) if the person to whom it is issued so desires; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the registering authority, for reasons to be communicated in writing to the applicant for`
  line `the certificate, considers in any case that the certificate should be issued for a shorter period;`
  line
  line `(c) subject to such other terms and conditions, including in particular, the maintenance by the`
  line `holder of the certificate of the prescribed records containing details of his financial transactions in`
  line `regard to recruitment, persons recruited or assisted to emigrate by him, employers concerned,`
  line `contracts and other arrangements entered into in connection with recruitment, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a certificate may contain, in addition to the prescribed terms and conditions, such`
  line `other terms and conditions as the registering authority may, for securing the purposes of this Act,`
  line `impose in any particular case.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (4186)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Renewal of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4186&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `A certificate may be renewed from time to time and the provisions of`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder (including provisions as to fees) shall apply to the renewal of a`
  line `certificate as they apply to the issue thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that no certificate shall be renewed unless, the application for its renewal is made not less`
  line `than three months prior to the date on which the certificate, would, but for such renewal, cease to be`
  line `valid:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the registering authority may entertain an application for the renewal of a`
  line `certificate which has been made at any time during the period of three months prior to the date on which`
  line `the certificate would, but for such renewal, cease to be valid if the applicant satisfied the registering`
  line `authority that he had sufficient cause for not making such application before the said period.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (4187)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Cancellation, suspension, etc., of a certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4187&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The registering authority may cancel any`
  line `certificate on any one or more of the following grounds and on no other ground namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that having regard to the manner in which the holder of the certificate has carried on his`
  line `business or any deterioration in his financial position, the facilities at his disposal for recruitment, the`
  line `holder of the certificate is not a fit person to continue to hold the certificate;`
  line
  line `(b) that the holder of the certificate has recruited emigrants for purposes prejudicial to the`
  line `interests of India or for purposes contrary to public policy;`
  line
  line `(c) that the holder of the certificate has, subsequent to the issue of the certificate, been convicted`
  line `in India for any offence involving moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(d) that the holder of the certificate has, subsequent to the issue of the certificate, been convicted`
  line `by a court in India for any offence under this Act, the Emigration Act, 1922 (7 of 1922), or any other`
  line `law relating to passports, foreign exchange, drugs, narcotics or smuggling and sentenced in respect`
  line `thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months;`
  line
  line `(e) that the certificate has been issued or renewed on misrepresentation or suppression of any`
  line `material fact;`
  line
  line `(f) that the holder of the certificate has violated any of the terms and conditions of the certificate;`
  line
  line `(g) that in the opinion of the Central Government it is necessary in the interests of friendly`
  line `relations of India with any foreign country or in the interests of the general public to cancel the`
  line certificate.
  line
  line `(2) Where the registering authority, for reasons to be recorded in writing, is satisfied that pending`
  line `the consideration of the question of cancelling any certificate on any of the grounds mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) it is necessary so to do, the registering authority may, by order in writing, suspend the`
  line `operation of the certificate for such period not exceeding thirty days as may be specified in the order and`
  line `require the holder of the certificate to show cause, within fifteen days from the date of receipt of such`
  line `order, as to why the suspension of the certificate should not be extended till the determination of the`
  line `question as to whether the registration should be cancelled.`
  line
  line `(3) A court convicting a holder of a certificate for an offence under this Act may also cancel the`
  line `certificate:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the conviction is set aside in appeal or otherwise, the cancellation under`
  line `sub-section (3) shall become void.`
  line
  line `(4) An order of cancellation of a certificate may be made under sub-section (3) by an appellate court`
  line `or by a court exercising its powers of revision.`
  line
  line `(5) Before passing an order cancelling or suspending a certificate the registering authority or the`
  line `court, as the case may be, shall consider the question as to the provisions and arrangements which should`
  line `be made for safeguarding the interests of emigrants and other persons with whom the holder of the`
  line `certificate had any transactions in the course of his business as recruiting agent and may make such orders`
  line `(including orders permitting the holder of the certificate to continue to carry on his business with respect`
  line `to all or any such emigrants and other persons) as it may consider necessary in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a certificate issued to any person has been cancelled under this section, such person shall`
  line `not be eligible to make any application for another certificate under this Chapter until the expiry of a`
  line `period of two years from the date of such cancellation.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (4188)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4188&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, appoint the Protector`
  line `General of Emigrants or any other officer of that Government of a rank higher than that of a Protector of`
  line `Emigrants to be the authority (hereinafter referred to as the competent authority) for issuing permits under`
  line `this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, authorise any person who is employed under that Government in any country or place`
  line `outside India to exercise the powers of the competent authority, and issue permits under this Chapter to`
  line `employers who are not citizens of India for the purpose of recruiting any citizen of India for employment`
  line `in such country or place and a person so authorised shall endorse a duly certified copy of every permit`
  line `issued by him under this Chapter to the Protector General of Emigrants.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (4189)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Recruitment by employers to be through recruiting agent or under permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4189&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Save as`
  line `otherwise provided by or under this Act, no employer shall recruit any citizen of India for employment in`
  line `any country or place outside India except--`
  line
  line `(a) through a recruiting agent competent under this Act to make such recruitment, or`
  line
  line `(b) in accordance with a valid permit issued in this behalf under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (4190)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Procedure for obtaining permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4190&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) An employer desiring to obtain a permit under this`
  line `Chapter may make an application in that behalf in the prescribed form to the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of such application, the competent authority shall, subject to any rules made in this`
  line `behalf, make such inquiry as he may deem necessary and grant the permit applied for or reject the`
  line `application:`
  line
  line `Provided that before granting a permit the competent authority may require the applicant to comply`
  line `with such conditions as may be prescribed, including conditions as to furnishing of security and such`
  line `other conditions as that authority may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, deem necessary in the`
  line `interests of the citizens of India likely to be recruited by the applicant.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the competent authority may reject an application`
  line `under sub-section (1) on any one or more of the following grounds and on no other ground, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the application is not complete in all respects or that any of the material particulars`
  line `furnished in the application are not true;`
  line
  line `(b) that the terms and conditions of employment which the applicant proposes to offer to persons`
  line `recruited or proposed to be recruited by him are discriminatory or exploitative;`
  line
  line `(c) that the employment which the applicant proposes to offer involves work of a nature which is`
  line `unlawful according to the laws of India or offends against the public policy of India or is violative of`
  line `norms of human dignity and decency;`
  line
  line `(d) that having regard to the antecedents of the applicant, his financial standing, the facilities at`
  line `his disposal, the working and living conditions of persons employed by him in the past, it would not`
  line `be in the public interest or in the interests of the persons who may be recruited by him, to issue a`
  line `permit to him;`
  line
  line `(e) that having regard to the prevailing circumstances in the country or in the place where the`
  line `applicant proposes to employ the persons recruited by him, it would not be in the interests of any`
  line `citizen of India to emigrate for taking up such employment.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the competent authority makes an order under sub-section (2) rejecting an application, he`
  line `shall record in writing a brief statement of his reasons for making such order and furnish the applicant, on`
  line `demand, a copy of the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the competent authority is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the`
  line `interests of friendly relations with a foreign country or in the interests of the general public so to do, he`
  line `may refuse to provide such copy or, as the case may be, furnish a copy of only such parts of the statement`
  line `as he may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (4191)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Period of validity of permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4191&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `A permit issued under section 17 shall be valid till the expiry of`
  line `such period, not exceeding one year, as may be prescribed, from the date of issue thereof, or till the`
  line `recruitment or the persons for whose recruitment such permit is issued is completed, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the holder of the permit has been unable for sufficient cause, to complete such`
  line `recruitment before the expiry of the prescribed period, the prescribed authority may, subject to rules made`
  line `in this behalf, extend the period of validity of the permit by such further period or periods, not exceeding`
  line `three months at a time.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (4192)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Registration of certain permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4192&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any permit obtained from a person authorised under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15 shall not be valid unless a certified copy thereof is filed in the prescribed`
  line `manner with the Protector General of Emigrants.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (4193)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Cancellation or suspension of a permit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4193&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 14 relating to cancellation`
  line `and suspension of a certificate referred to therein shall, subject to such modifications as may be necessary`
  line `(including modifications for construing the references in that section to registering authority as references`
  line `to competent authority under this Chapter), apply for the cancellation or suspension of a permit.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (4194)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4194&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, if satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so`
  line `to do in the public interest, by notification and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in`
  line `the notification, exempt any class or classes of employers from the requirement of obtaining a permit`
  line `under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (4195)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Requirement, etc., as to emigration clearance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4195&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) No citizen of India shall emigrate unless he`
  line `obtains under this Chapter from the Protector of Emigrants authorisation in the prescribed manner and`
  line `form (such authorisation being hereinafter referred to as emigration clearance) for emigration.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for emigration clearance shall be in the prescribed form, shall contain the`
  line `prescribed particulars and shall be made by the emigrant concerned to the Protector of Emigrants:`
  line
  line `Provided that such application may be made through the recruiting agent, if any, through whom the`
  line `emigrant has been recruited or through the employer concerned.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application under sub-section (2) shall be accompanied by--`
  line
  line `(a) a true copy (verified and authenticated in the prescribed manner) of the agreement with`
  line `respect to the employment for the taking up of which the applicant proposes to emigrate and where`
  line `such agreement does not provide for all or any of the prescribed matters, also a statement (verified`
  line `and authenticated in the prescribed manner) setting out the particulars with respect to such matters;`
  line
  line `(b) a statement (verified and authenticated in the prescribed manner) as to the provision by way`
  line `of security for meeting the expenses which may be incurred in case it becomes necessary to arrange`
  line `for the repatriation to India of the applicant;`
  line
  line `(c) a receipt evidencing the payment of the prescribed fee;`
  line
  line `(d) such other relevant documents or copies of relevant documents as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Protector of Emigrants shall, after satisfying himself about the accuracy of the particulars`
  line `mentioned in the application and in the other documents submitted along with the application, authorise`
  line `in the prescribed manner and form, the emigration of the applicant or intimate by order in writing the`
  line `applicant or, as the case may be, the recruiting agent or employer through whom the applications have`
  line `been made about the deficiencies and required him to make good such deficiencies within such time as`
  line `may be specified in the order or reject the application.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the Protector of Emigrants may reject an application`
  line `for emigration clearance under this section on any one or more of the following grounds and on no other`
  line `ground, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the terms and conditions of employment which the applicant proposes to take up are`
  line `discriminatory or exploitative;`
  line
  line `(b) that the employment which the applicant proposes to take up involves work of a nature which`
  line `is unlawful according to the laws of India or offends against the public policy of India or is violative`
  line `of norms of human dignity and decency;`
  line
  line `(c) that the applicant will have to work or live in sub-standard working or living conditions;`
  line
  line `(d) that having regard to the prevailing circumstances in the country or place where the applicant`
  line `proposes to take up employment or the antecedents of the employer under whom the applicant`
  line `proposes to take up employment or any other relevant circumstances, it would not be in the interests`
  line `of the applicant to emigrate;`
  line
  line `(e) that no provision or arrangement has been made for meeting the expenses which may be`
  line `incurred in case it becomes necessary to arrange for the repatriation to India of the applicant, or that`
  line `the provisions or arrangements made in this behalf are not adequate for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(6) Every order rejecting an application for emigration clearance shall set out clearly the ground or`
  line `grounds on which the order has been made and the facts or circumstances on which such ground or`
  line `grounds are based.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (4196)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4196&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by--`
  line
  line `(a) an order of the registering authority rejecting his application for registration or requiring him`
  line `to furnish any security or to comply with any term or condition (not being a prescribed term or`
  line `condition) specified in the certificate issued to him or suspending or cancelling or refusing to renew`
  line `the certificate issued to him; or`
  line
  line `(b) an order of the competent authority rejecting his application for a permit or requiring him to`
  line `comply with any terms or conditions (not being a prescribed term or condition) specified in the permit`
  line `issued to him, or suspending or cancelling or refusing to extend the period of the validity of the`
  line `permit issued to him; or`
  line
  line `(c) an order of the Protector of Emigrants rejecting his application for emigration clearance; or`
  line
  line `(d) an order of the registering authority or the competent authority or the Protector of Emigrants`
  line `or the prescribed authority requiring him to furnish any security, additional security or fresh security`
  line `under this Act, or forfeiting or rejecting his claim for refund (whether wholly or partly in either case)`
  line `of the security, the additional security or the fresh security furnished by him;`
  line
  line `may prefer an appeal against such order to the Central Government within such period as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall be admitted if it is preferred after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor if the`
  line `appellant satisfies the Central Government that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within`
  line `that period.`
  line
  line `(3) The period prescribed for an appeal shall be computed in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), with respect to the computation of periods thereunder.`
  line
  line `(4) Every appeal under this section shall be made in such form as may be prescribed and shall be`
  line `accompanied by a copy of the order appealed against and by such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure for disposing of an appeal (including remand of the matter for further consideration`
  line `to the authority whose order has been appealed against) shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that before disposing of an appeal, the appellant shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `representing his case.`
  line
  line `(6) Every order made on an appeal under this section confirming, modifying or reversing the order`
  line `appealed against shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (4197)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4197&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) except in conformity with the provisions of this Act emigrates; or`
  line
  line `(b) contravenes the provisions of section 10 or section 16; or`
  line
  line `(c) by intentionally furnishing any false information or suppressing any material information`
  line `obtains a certificate or a permit or an emigration clearance under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) without lawful authority makes or causes to be made any alteration in any certificate or permit`
  line `or in any document or endorsement by way of emigration clearance issued or made under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(e) disobeys or neglects to comply with any order of the Protector of Emigrants under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(f) collects from an emigrant any charges in excess of the limits prescribed under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(g) cheats any emigrant;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and with fine which`
  line `may extend to two thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of any special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in`
  line `the judgment of the court, such imprisonment shall not be less than six months and such fine shall not be`
  line `less than one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever attempts to commit any offence under sub-section (1) shall be punishable with the`
  line `punishment provided for such offence under that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes any term or condition subject to which any emigration clearance has been`
  line `given under this Act, shall, if no other punishment is provided elsewhere in this Act for such`
  line `contravention, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with fine`
  line `which may extend to two thousand rupees or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever abets any offence punishable under this Act shall, if the act abetted is committed in`
  line `consequence of the abetment, be punishable with the punishment provided for that offence.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever, having been convicted of an offence under any provision of this Act is again convicted`
  line `of an offence under the same provision, shall be punishable, for the second and for each subsequent`
  line `offence, with double the penalty provided for that offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (4198)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4198&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence, and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (4199)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4199&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all offences under this Act shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (4200)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Previous sanction of Central Government necessary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4200&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution shall be instituted`
  line `against any person in respect of any offence under this Act without the previous sanction of the Central`
  line `Government or such officer or authority as may be authorised by that Government by order in writing in`
  line `this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that no sanction shall be required when an offence has been committed in respect of an`
  line `emigrant or an intending emigrant and the complaint is filed by such emigrant or intending emigrant, or`
  line `on behalf of such emigrant or intending emigrant, by the father, mother, husband, wife, son, daughter,`
  line `brother, sister or guardian of such emigrant or intending emigrant, or if such emigrant or intending`
  line `emigrant is a member of a joint Hindu family, by the manager of that family.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (4201)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Punishment to be without prejudice to any other action.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4201&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The award of punishment for an`
  line `offence under this Act shall be without prejudice to any other action which has been or which may be`
  line `taken under this Act with respect to such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (4202)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Determination of question as to whether a person is an emigrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4202&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Where a question arises`
  line `before a Protector of Emigrants as to whether a person intending to depart from India is or is not an`
  line `emigrant, the Protector of Emigrants shall decide the question after holding an inquiry in such manner and`
  line `upon considering such evidence as may be prescribed and such other evidence as may be relevant, and`
  line `communicate the decision to such person in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (4203)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to prohibit emigration to any country in the interests of the general public, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4203&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government has reason to believe that sufficient grounds exist for`
  line `prohibiting emigration to any country, having regard to the sovereignty and integrity of India, the security`
  line `of India, friendly relations of India with any foreign country or the interests of the general public, it may,`
  line `by notification, prohibit emigration to that country.`
  line
  line `(2) A notification issued under sub-section (1) shall have effect for such period not exceeding six`
  line `months as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government has reason to believe that the grounds mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) continue to exist, it may, from time to time, by notification, prohibit emigration to that`
  line `country for such further period, not exceeding six months on each occasion, as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (4204)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to prohibit emigration due to outbreak of epidemics, civil disturbances, etc., in a country.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4204&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government has reason to believe--`
  line
  line `(a) that intending emigrants if allowed to emigrate to any country would be exposed to serious`
  line `risk to life on arrival there by reason of--`
  line
  line `(i) outbreak of any disease or grave pollution of environment in such country, or`
  line
  line `(ii) outbreak of hostilities or civil war or civil commotion or political disturbances;`
  line
  line `(b) that by reason of India not being in diplomatic relations with that country it is not possible to`
  line `protect the emigrants from discrimination, maltreatment and exploitation,`
  line
  line `it may, by notification, prohibit emigration to that country.`
  line
  line `(2) A notification issued under sub-section (1) shall have effect for such period not exceeding six`
  line `months as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government has reason to believe that any ground mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) continues to exist, it may, from time to time, by notification, prohibit emigration to that`
  line `country for such further period, not exceeding six months on each occasion, as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (4205)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to prohibit emigration of any class or category of persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4205&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central`
  line `Government considers that in the interests of the general public, immigration of any class or category of`
  line `persons, having regard to their age, sex or other relevant factors, to any country should be prohibited, it`
  line `may, by notification, prohibit the emigration to such country of such class or category of persons as may`
  line `be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A notification issued under sub-section (1) shall have effect for such period not exceeding six`
  line `months as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government has reason to believe that any of the grounds mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) continues to exist, it may, from time to time, by notification, prohibit emigration of such`
  line `class or category of persons to that country for such further period, not exceeding six months on each`
  line `occasion, as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (4206)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Provisions as to security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4206&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any security or other financial provision which may be required`
  line `to be made under this Act shall be reasonable having regard to the purpose for which such security or`
  line `other financial provision is required to be made.`
  line
  line `(2) The prescribed authority may, after giving notice in the prescribed manner to a person who has`
  line `furnished any security for any purpose and after giving to such person an opportunity to represent his`
  line `case, by order in writing, direct that the whole or any part of such security may be forfeited for being`
  line `utilised for such purpose and in such manner as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) Where it appears to the prescribed authority that the security furnished by any person under this`
  line `Act for any purpose has, for any reason, become inadequate, or has ceased to be available for any reason`
  line `whatsoever, the prescribed authority may, after giving him an opportunity to represent his case, by order`
  line `in writing, require such person to furnish such additional security or, as the case may be, such fresh`
  line `security as may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (4207)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Refund of security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4207&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any security furnished under this Act shall be refunded or, as the case may`
  line `be, released, when no longer required for the purpose for which it has been furnished and the other`
  line `circumstances in which and the manner in which any security furnished under this Act may be released or`
  line `refunded shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (4208)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to search, seize and detain persons, conveyance, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4208&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `All the powers for the time being`
  line `conferred by the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), on officers of customs with regard to the searching and`
  line `detention of persons, vessels or aircraft or any other conveyance, or seizure of any document or thing or`
  line `arrest of any person or otherwise for the purpose of prevention or detection of any offence under that Act`
  line `or for apprehending a person suspected to have committed any offence under that Act may be exercised,`
  line `for the purpose of prevention or detection of any offence under this Act or for apprehending a person`
  line `suspected to have committed any offence under this Act, by--`
  line
  line `(a) any such officer of customs, or`
  line
  line `(b) the Protector General of Emigrants or a Protector of Emigrants, or`
  line
  line `(c) an officer in charge of an emigration check-post.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (4209)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Returns and registers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4209&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every recruiting agent shall maintain such registers and other`
  line `records and shall submit to the prescribed authorities such periodical or other returns as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The Protector General of Emigrants, the registering authority, the competent authority or a`
  line `Protector of Emigrants may, by order, call for any other return or information from a recruiting agent.`
  line
  line `(3) The Protector General of Emigrants, the registering authority, the competent authority or a`
  line `Protector of Emigrants or an officer in charge of an emigration check-post may inspect any register or`
  line `other record maintained by a recruiting agent under sub-section (1) and for the purpose of such`
  line `inspection, enter, at any reasonable time, the business premises of a recruiting agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (4210)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Authorities and officers to have certain powers of civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4210&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Protector General of`
  line `Emigrants, the registering authority, the competent authority and every Protector of Emigrants shall, for`
  line `the purpose of discharging their functions under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a court`
  line `under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while trying a suit, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(d) receiving evidence on affidavits; and`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding before the Protector General of Emigrants, or the registering authority or the`
  line `competent authority or a Protector of Emigrants shall be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of`
  line `sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Protector General of Emigrants, the`
  line `registering authority, the competent authority, and every Protector of Emigrants shall be deemed to be a`
  line `civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2`
  line `of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (4211)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4211&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give directions to the Protector`
  line `General of Emigrants, the registering authority, the competent authority or any Protector of Emigrants as`
  line `to the carrying into execution of any provision of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (4212)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Effect of other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4212&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act or any rule made thereunder shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this Act or`
  line `in any agreement or other instrument having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as provided in sub-section (1), the provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and not in`
  line `derogation of, any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (4213)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4213&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, direct that any power or function--`
  line
  line `(a) which may be exercised or performed by it under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) which may be exercised or performed by a registering authority, a competent authority or a`
  line `Protector of Emigrants under this Act,`
  line
  line `may, in relation to such matters, and subject to such conditions, if any, as it may specify in the`
  line `notification, be also exercised or performed--`
  line
  line `(i) by such officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by any State Government or by any officer or authority subordinate to such State`
  line `Government, or`
  line
  line `(iii) in any foreign country in which there is no diplomatic mission of India, by such foreign`
  line `consular office,`
  line
  line `as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (4214)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4214&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government, on a reference made to it or otherwise, is`
  line `satisfied that having regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the friendly relations with any foreign country; or`
  line
  line `(b) the known reputation of any foreign employer or class of foreign employers, for providing to`
  line `emigrants standard conditions of living and working, and their methods of recruitment and conditions`
  line `of employment; or`
  line
  line `(c) the methods of recruitment followed and the conditions of employment provided by a public`
  line `undertaking or an approved concern for the execution of its projects abroad; or`
  line
  line `(d) the facilities and conditions of service provided by Government officers posted abroad to their`
  line `domestic servants accompanying such Government officers, where the expenditure in respect of the`
  line `passage of such domestic servants is borne by the Government; and`
  line
  line `(e) all other relevant considerations,`
  line `it is necessary or expedient in the public interest so to do, the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, exempt from the operation`
  line `of all or any of the provisions of this Act, such foreign dignitary or class of foreign employers, public`
  line `undertaking, approved concern or Government officers.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this sub-section--`
  line
  line `(a) "public undertaking" means--`
  line
  line `(i) an undertaking owned and controlled by Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956); or`
  line
  line `(iii) a body corporate established by or under any Central, Provincial or State Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "approved concern" means such company incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of`
  line `1956) or partnership firm registered under the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932), or society`
  line `registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) or any other law relating to`
  line `societies for the time being in force in any State, or co-operative society registered under any Central,`
  line `Provincial or State law, as the Central Government may, by notification, approve for the purposes of`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary for implementing any treaty, agreement`
  line `or convention between India and a foreign country or foreign countries so to do, it may, by notification,`
  line `and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, exempt from the operation`
  line `of all or any of the provisions of this Act, recruitment by such authorities, agencies or persons as may be`
  line `specified in the notification either generally or for such purposes as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (4215)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Act not to apply to certain emigrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4215&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall be deemed to apply`
  line to--
  line
  line `(a) the recruitment or emigration of any person who is not a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(b) the control of recruiting in India for the service of foreign States to which the Foreign`
  line `Recruiting Act, 1874 (4 of 1874) applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (4216)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4216&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the powers and duties of officers and employees appointed for the purposes of this Act and the`
  line `terms and conditions of their service;`
  line
  line `(b) the form of--`
  line
  line `(i) a certificate to commence or carry on the business of recruitment, and of an application for`
  line `the issue or renewal thereof;`
  line
  line `(ii) a permit for the recruitment of persons for employment outside India, and of an`
  line `application for the issue thereof;`
  line
  line `(iii) an application for emigration clearance;`
  line
  line `(iv) an appeal to be preferred to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner and form in which an authorisation by way of emigration clearance may be given;`
  line
  line `(d) particulars to be contained in an application for a certificate or a permit or for an emigration`
  line clearance;
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which different inquiries required to be held under this Act may be held;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which the amount of security for securing the due performance of the terms and`
  line `conditions of the certificate or permit or for compliance with the provisions of this Act shall be`
  line furnished;
  line
  line `(g) the manner of verifying or authenticating documents and copies of documents for the`
  line `purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure to be followed in hearing an appeal preferred to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(i) the fees to be paid in respect of applications and other matters under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) the charges which a recruiting agent may recover from an emigrant in respect of services`
  line `rendered and the scales and limits of such charges;`
  line
  line `(k) the terms and conditions subject to which a certificate or a permit or an emigration clearance`
  line `may be issued under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) the period of the validity of a certificate or a permit issued under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) the authority competent to extend the period of validity of a permit or to forfeit security or to`
  line `require any additional security or fresh security under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) the accommodation, the provisions, the medical stores and staff, the life saving and sanitary`
  line `arrangements and other provisions and arrangement for the well-being, security and protection of`
  line `emigrants which shall be provided and the records which shall be maintained in any emigrant`
  line conveyance.
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (4217)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Notifications and rules to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857&sectionId=4217&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00032_198331_1517807325857
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Every notification issued under`
  line `clause (o) of sub-section (1) of section 2, section 30, section 31 or section 32 and every rule made under`
  line `section 43 shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued or made, before each House of Parliament,`
  line `while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or`
  line `more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the notification or the`
  line `rule or both Houses agree that the notification or the rule should not be issued or made, the notification or`
  line `the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that notification or rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
